(594, 'gad', 'Standing Forward Bend with Clasped Hands', 'Stand with your feet hip-width apart and fold forward at your hips, keeping your knees slightly bent. Clasp your hands behind your back and lift your arms towards the ceiling, allowing gravity to pull them towards your head. Feel the stretch in your shoulders, upper back, and hamstrings. Hold for a few breaths, then slowly come back up to standing.', 'eximg/Standing Forward Bend with Clasped Hands.jpg', 'Beginner', 'Back'),
